HEADWORD: Koftgari
<hw>Koft`ga*ri"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>koft gar⟦ium⟧</ets> goldbeating. fr. Per. <ets>koft</ets> beating +
<ets>gar⟦ium⟧</ets> trade.]</ety> <def>Ornamental work produced by
inlaying steel with gold, -- a variety of damascening much used in the
arts of India.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kogia</ent>⟦br⟧
